div1.p:
Stephen Bass. On the 15th of Jan. I met with a young woman (name Rose Manning) who asked me to give her a pot of beer, so we went into a publick house and I called for a pot of beer, there was another woman (her name was
Bess Avery
) in that house, who had some knowledge of me; she said, you are not used to drink beer, let us have a pot of hot, so I called for a pot of hot, and after that for another, till we had five, which I paid for; then they wanted to have another, but I had no more silver, so pulled out my money and changed a guinea. After that we went into another room; then they said they were hungry, so I sent for some victuals and had it or fled ; I sat drinking with those two till about 12 o'clock at night after supper .
